    {
      "id": "port-canva-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Canva Brief",
      "position": {
        "x": -120,
        "y": -140
      },
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Canva Brief: Twilite Ports\n\nDesign a calmer visual language for graph ports.\n\nPorts are functionally necessary, but they currently look too loud and widget-like.\n\nThey should read as **boundary affordances**: quiet when idle, clear when needed, and strongly magnetic only during connection work.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "identity": {
