    {
      "id": "port-canva-projected",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Projected Port Special Case",
      "position": {
        "x": 900,
        "y": 120
      },
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Projected Port Special Case\n\nSometimes a standalone `port` node projects onto a host node boundary.\n\nFor this case:\n- the projected boundary affordance should look like part of the host\n- the standalone port node should become visually secondary unless focused\n- host ownership should remain obvious",
